<h1 id="publish-and-manage-datasets">Publish and manage datasets</h1>
<p>Central government, local authorities and public bodies can publish on the data.gov.uk directory.</p>
<p>Data.gov.uk does not host datasets. Instead, you must first publish the dataset (or supporting document) on your organisation’s website, on GOV.UK or on your service&rsquo;s own hosting.</p>
<p>You can then add the dataset to the data.gov.uk directory, which will display a description and a link to the dataset.</p>
<p>Find out how to:</p>

<ul>
<li><a href="get_and_manage_accounts/#get-an-account">get an account</a></li>
<li><a href="get_and_manage_accounts/#add-or-remove-editors-and-admins">manage an existing account</a></li>
<li><a href="harvest_or_add_data/#harvest-or-add-data">harvest or add data</a></li>
<li><a href="managing_published_data/#managing-published-data">manage published data</a></li>
</ul>
<p>If you’d like to showcase your data by making it part of the new <a href="https://data.gov.uk">curated data collections</a>, you can express your interest through our <a href="https://forms.office.com/e/9V26PNFQaR">feedback form</a>.</p>
